<TEXT>
Mr Donald Trump, the US property developer, said yesterday he had no
intention of selling his 51 per cent stake in the landmark Plaza Hotel in
New York, but said his company had been approached by people interested in
acquiring a stake in the Plaza, Reuter reports from New York.
Mr Trump told CNBC cable television that his company had had contacts with
the representative of the Sultan of Brunei, who is considered one of the
world's richest people.
'The Sultan of Brunei, his people have spoken to us, various other people
have spoken to us and we may do some kind of partnership or something,' Mr
Trump said.
The New York Post had earlier reported that the sultan and his partners had
bid more than Dollars 300m for the Fifth Avenue hotel.
However, Trump Organisation chief executive Mr Nicholas Ribis said there had
been no substantive discussions.
