<HEAD>Sultan of Brunei Spends $950,000 on Birthday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Sultan of Brunei, one of the world's richest
men, reportedly spent at least $950,000 on his nephew's ninth
birthday party.
   The Sunday Express said the sultan converted a ballroom at
Claridge's in London into a replica of Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
headquarters.
   An army of workers turned the ballroom into a giant New York
City sewer for the party for young Prince Bahar, the paper said.
Four men dressed as the superheros, Donatello, Leonardo,
Michelangeo and Raphael, mingled with the young guests.
   A group of luxurious anterooms were transformed into a network
of gurglig drains, the paper said. Music was provided by the pop
duo Partners in Kryme, who were flown to London to perform their
hit ``Turtle Power,'' the newspaper said.
   Claridge's banqueting staff served pizza in a neon-lit pizza
parlor, The Sunday Express said. It did not say what day the party
took place.
   ``It was an incredible sight,'' said one member of Claridge's
staff, who spoke to the newspaper on condition of anonymity.
   The report could not be independently confirmed.
