   By PHILIP STEPHENS, Political Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A GROUP of Labour MPs last night accused the High Commission of Brunei in
London of failing to honour debts incurred by sponsored students from the
Sultanate.
In a motion tabled under parliamentary privilege, the MPs called on the
Sultan of Brunei to 'meet the debts owed by his High Commission to landlords
and other debts in the United Kingdom'.
The MPs, led by Mr Nigel Griffiths (Edinburgh South), said the commission
