  [Text] Thailand has reaffirmed its readiness to fully 
cooperate with Brunei Darussalam in various areas both under 
bilateral relation and within the ASEAN framework. Bruneian 
Foreign Minister Prince Mohamed Bolkiah held talks with Prime 
Minister Chuan Likphai on Friday on bilateral cooperation. He 
concluded his three-day visit to Thailand yesterday. 
  Prime Minister Chuan said he hoped that Brunei would 
increase 
its investment in the region. He also expressed his 
appreciation to the Bruneian Government for taking good care of 
Thai workers in that country. The Bruneian foreign minister 
praised Thai workers for their efficiency, saying that Brunei is 
still in need of foreign labor as the country is accelerating 
the construction of infrastructure. He said Brunei would learn 
from successes in national development in various countries, 
Thailand included. The country will host the next ASEAN 
ministerial meeting after Thailand. 
  Both sides will work out the program for the visit to 
Thailand by Sultan Haji Hassanal Bolkiah of Brunei as guest of 
His Majesty the King of Thailand. 

