<HEAD>London's Dorchester Hotel To Close For Facelift</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Dorchester, one of London's most exclusive
hotels, will close in December for more than a year for a $134
million facelift.
   It will be the first closure in the hotel's 57-year history.
   The hotel, situated in Park Lane, was bought for $80 million
three years ago by the world's richest man, the Sultan of Brunei,
who pledged to make it the most luxurious in the world.
   A hotel spokesman said on Tuesday that major improvements
include an Oriental restaurant, a nightclub, a health club and news
conference rooms. The kitchens, plumbing and electrical system also
are to be upgraded.
   The hotel will close on Dec. 23 and reopen sometime in the
spring of 1990.
</TEXT>
